text: Elizabeth Tan Su Mei (; born 18 November 1993) is a Malaysian singer, model and actress. She became publicly known for her song titled "Knock Knock", released in 2014. Prior to her stardom, Lizzy, as she is fondly known starting her early career uploading videos on YouTube where she sang some cover songs. Tan's music career gain wider recognition when she won Best Female Artist award at the 14th Anugerah Planet Muzik. As an actress. she is widely known for her role as Dilaila in 2019 psychological horror film Misteri Dilaila directed by Syafiq Yusof. ==Music career== Her career as a singer began when she uploaded videos on YouTube where she sang some cover songs. ==Discography== ===Singles=== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" style="text-align:center;" border="1" ! scope="col" style="width:16em;" | Title ! scope="col" style="width:5em;" | Year |- ! scope="row" | "Knock Knock" | 2014 |- ! scope="row" | "The World Can Wait" | rowspan="3" | 2015 |- ! scope="row" | "Somewhere New" (Goldfish & Blink feat.
